fields.description:
While troubleshooting a customer issue, they attempted to run {{euctl}} without any args, and then hit this:

{code}
# euctl
authentication.access_keys_limit = 2
authentication.authorization_cache = maximumSize=1000, expireAfterWrite=1m
authentication.authorization_expiry = 5s
authentication.authorization_reuse_expiry = 0s
authentication.credential_download_generate_certificate = Absent
authentication.credential_download_host_match =
authentication.credential_download_port =
authentication.default_password_expiry = 60d
euctl: error: Expecting property name: line 17 column 3 (char 1363)
{code}

On reviewing the euca-describe-properties output for the same cloud, we noted a rather substantially sized chunk of text for {{authentication.ldap_integration_configuration}}.

Before making any changes to this property in the PRC, we had a look at the current value:

{code}
[root@odc-c-07 ~]# euctl authentication.ldap_integration_configuration
[root@odc-c-07 ~]# euctl --dump authentication.ldap_integration_configuration
{
  "sync": {
    "enable": "false"
  }
}
{code}

We had the customer run these 2 commands, just to see whether either would succeed:

{code}
# euctl authentication.ldap_integration_configuration
euctl: error: Expecting property name: line 17 column 3 (char 1363)

# euctl --dump authentication.ldap_integration_configuration
euctl: error: Expecting property name: line 17 column 3 (char 1363)
{code}

